The paper proposes a novel tracker based on DCF framework for UAV tracking, which involves computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO). The proposed method involves introducing historical views in training to improve the model's robustness, which can be considered as a form of memory-based learning (LG). The paper also proposes a novel rapid compressed context learning to increase the discriminative ability of the filter, which involves machine learning (MM) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.AI.
